Date: Thu, 02 Sep 1999 21:43:01 -0700
From: David J. Rogers <djr@onlinemac.com>

So... who in this rural area is dealing with testing and reporting? How
were the animals captured and tested? Who does the testing? Using what
methods? What type of post exposure prophylaxis regimen was used with the
human exposures? Which agency evaluated the risks inherent with each
exposure? I am asking these questions because there doesn't seem to be a
standard nationwide protocol in use. I have referred several possible
exposures to county health here in Oregon, USA, and have not been impressed
with the knowledge or evaluation of risk for the patients I have referred.
Any info you could provide would be of help.
--
David J. Rogers
Director
Wilderness Medical Consultants
e-mail: djr@onlinemac.com
