[3
Date: Thu, 02 Sep 1999 19:10:20 -0400
From: Eleanor Kellon <kell@epix.net>

Sounds like it might be a good idea for the local veterinary association to
consider sponsoring a low cost rabies vaccination clinic, even a mobile
vaccination clinic in a van, etc. to get more of these dogs and cats
covered. We've done several here in Pennsylvania and the turnout is
excellent. Vets, and technicians volunteer their time; owners pay cost
only. Local papers are informed and their stories serve to advertise the
clinics. TV/radio can be involved too, as a public service. Owners know
they should be getting these vaccinations but for financial or whatever
reasons often don't. Making it an "event" seems to motivate them better.
--
Eleanor M. Kellon, V.M.D.
e-mail: kell@epix.net
